<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900518-0182</DOCNO><DOCID>900518-0182.</DOCID><HL>   Italy Commercial Vehicle Sales</HL><DATE>05/18/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   EUROP F</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   MILAN -- New commercial vehicle sales in Italy rose 0.4%in April from the year before and were up 7.2% in the firstfour months of 1990, according to figures released by theItalian Federation of Auto Manufacturers, Anfia.   Sales of the commercial vehicles, which are small busesand trucks weighing up to 3.5 tons, totaled 13,501 in April,compared with 13,448 in April 1989, Anfia said. During thefirst four months of the year, commercial vehicle salestotaled 59,260, compared with 55,297 in the first four monthsof 1988.</LP><TEXT>   Domestic manufacturers controlled 49.8% of the market,while Ford Motor Co. was a leader among foreign manufacturerswith a 14% market share.</TEXT></DOC>